description: Laxalt is in a dead heat with incumbent Senator Catherine Cortez Masto, who's in her first term representing Nevada and is one of the most vulnerable Democrats running for re-election.

title: Netflix is slammed for 'rewriting' the Queen's Annus Horribilis speech for The Crown
description: Netflix was slammed for making up royal scenes for The Crown and are forced to rewrite the Queen's historic Annus Horribilis speech on Friday.

title: Quality Street could shrink its tub selection by THREE sweets this Christmas
description: The classic Quality street tub could lose an average of three chocolates this year with some of the nation's most-loved festive favourites dropped, new analysis reveals.

title: Queensland carjack: Man with a large machete tries to get into a car at Deception Bay
description: The unsettling footage, taken on Monday at Deception Bay in Queensland, shows the man tapping on the window of a car and demanding the driver let him in.

title: China's zero-Covid policy no longer about health... It's about power and mass surveillance
description: IAN WILLIAMS: Last weekend, Li Qiang, the Communist Party boss of Shanghai, was rewarded for his zero-Covid fanaticism. He was promoted by party leader Xi Jinping (pictured).

title: Union calls for better pay and conditions for Britain's millions of night shift workers
description: The Trades Union Congress (TUC) has said many of those working overnight are on low pay and insecure contracts.

title: Altona Meadows: Miraculous escape of  11-year-old Jake Gilbert after he was caught in floodwaters
description: A boy has thanked his rescuers after he was sucked down a stormwater drain by a raging torrent of floodwater while riding his bike in Melbourne's south-west.

title: How the SAS was forged from public schools and prisons as BBC blockbuster to reveal its origins
description: That boy Stirling is mad, quite mad.' That was Field Marshal Bernard Montgomery's verdict on the maverick officer David Stirling (pictured), after he came looking to recruit Monty's best men.

title: Gina Rinehart: Forgotten story about mining magnate's Aboriginal half-sister to 'racist' dad
description: Mining magnate Lang Hancock was thrusted back into the spotlight this month after the company bearing his name tore up a $15million sponsorship for Netball Australia.

title: Average UK household is hoarding £800 of unworn fashion in their wardrobes
description: More than four in ten (43 per cent) have bought an item online, not liked it but kept it anyway. With 59 per cent of those who've done this admitting they 'couldn't be bothered' to return it.
